article.description: — Carter Hendricksen had a career-high 27 points as North Florida snapped its 13-game road losing streak, topping Jacksonville State 88-76 on Thursday night. Jose Placer added 25 points for the Ospreys.
article.headline: North Florida tops Jacksonville St. 88-76
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Ala. -- — Carter Hendricksen had a career-high 27 points as North Florida snapped its 13-game road losing streak, topping Jacksonville State 88-76 on Thursday night. Jose Placer added 25 points for the Ospreys. Jarius Hicklen had 11 points for North Florida (6-17, 2-7 Atlantic Sun Conference). Brandon Huffman had 19 points for the Gamecocks (15-7, 8-1), whose 10-game winning streak was snapped. Darian Adams added 16 points and seven rebounds.
